Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that the balance of a medium prime `p` (where `√n < p ≤ n/L`) is at least `-M`.

The balance is defined as:
```lean
balance p = (sum of p-adic valuations in factorization) - (p-adic valuation of n!)
```

I need to show this is `≥ -M`, which is equivalent to showing:
```lean
(sum of p-adic valuations) ≥ (p-adic valuation of n!) - M
```

Looking at the similar theorem `balance_medium_prime_le`, I can follow a symmetric approach. The key insight is that:
1. The p-adic valuation of `n!` equals `n/p` for primes `p > √n` (by `factorial_factorization_eq_div`)
2. The sum of p-adic valuations in the initial factorization is bounded by the count computation

Here's the proof:

```lean
theorem Params.initial.balance_medium_prime_ge (P : Params) {p : ℕ} (hp : p ≤ P.n / P.L) (hp' : p > Real.sqrt P.n) : P.initial.balance p ≥ -P.M := by
  by_cases hprime : p.Prime
  · have : (P.initial.a.map (·.factorization p)).sum ≥ P.n / p - P.M := by
      calc (P.initial.a.map (·.factorization p)).sum
        _ ≥ P.M * (Finset.filter (p ∣ ·) (.Ico (P.n - P.n / P.M) P.n)).card - P.M := by
            have h := sum_valuation_le_M_mul_interval_count P hp'
            omega
        _ ≥ P.M * ((P.n / P.M) / p) - P.M := by
            have : (Finset.filter (p ∣ ·) (.Ico (P.n - P.n / P.M) P.n)).card ≥ (P.n / P.M) / p - 1 := by
              have h := count_multiples_le (P.n - P.n / P.M) P.n p hprime.pos
              have : (P.n - (P.n - P.n / P.M) + p - 1) / p = (P.n / P.M + p - 1) / p := by
                rw [Nat.sub_sub_self (div_le_self _ _)]
              omega
            omega
        _ ≥ P.n / p - P.M := by
            have : P.M * ((P.n / P.M) / p) ≥ P.n / p - P.M := by
              have h := div_mul_le_self (P.n / P.M) p
              have h2 := mul_div_le P.n P.M
              omega
            omega
    simp only [Factorization.balance, Factorization.sum, factorial_factorization_eq_div hprime hp']
    omega
  · simp_all [Factorization.balance, Factorization.sum]
```
